[35m│[0m <h2>Introduction to EternalBlue</h2>\n    <p>\n        EternalBlue is a      [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m cyberattack exploit developed by the U.S. National Security Agency (NSA). It [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m targets a vulnerability in Microsoft\'s implementation of the Server Message [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m Block (SMB) protocol. This exploit became widely known when it was leaked by [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m a group called the Shadow Brokers in April 2017.\n    </p>\n\n               [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m <h2>Technical Overview</h2>\n    <p>\n        The exploit takes advantage of [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m a vulnerability in Windows systems in the SMBv1 server (MS17-010). By        [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m sending specially crafted packets, it is able to execute arbitrary code on   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m the target machine, allowing full access. This is typically the first step   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m in a multi-layered attack strategy that includes deploying ransomware or     [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m other malicious payloads.\n    </p>\n    <img style="max-height: 600px;"     [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m src="static/images/EternalBlue-3.webp" class="img-fluid mb-4">\n\n           [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m <h2>Impact on Global Cybersecurity</h2>\n    <p>\n        After the leak,    [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m EternalBlue was used to launch extensive cyberattacks, including the         [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m infamous WannaCry ransomware attack in May 2017. This attack affected over   [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m 200,000 computers across 150 countries, with total damages ranging into the  [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m billions of dollars. The exploit\'s ability to spread within networks        [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m without user interaction makes it particularly dangerous and effective as a  [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m tool for rapid dissemination of malware.\n    </p>\n    <img                 [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m style="max-height: 600px;" src="static/images/EternalBlue-2.webp"            [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m class="img-fluid mb-4">\n\n    <h2>Legacy and Continued Relevance</h2>\n     [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m <p>\n        Despite patches being released by Microsoft, many unpatched     [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m systems are still vulnerable to EternalBlue, and it remains in use by        [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m cybercriminals. The legacy of EternalBlue highlights the importance of       [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m regular system updates and the potential dangers of stockpiling cyber        [35m│[0m
[35m│[0m weapons.\n    </p>\n</div>            </div>\n\n            <!-- Sidebar     [35m│[0m
